<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Parliamentary Power Strengthened </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203155394 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1400 
GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The vote of no confidence in Slovak Prime Minister 
Vladimir Meciar has also decided whether authoritarian or 
parliamentary rule would prevail in Slovakia. This was stated 
today by Slovak President Michal Kovac in an exclusive interview 
for Slovak Television. He added that the National Council 
[parliament] made a clear-cut decision to continue strengthening 
the system of parliamentary power. Thus it has sent a very 
positive signal abroad, where doubts were sometimes cast as to 
whether we really try to strengthen democracy and constitutional 
rule, President Kovac said. At the same time, he emphasized 
that the parliament decided freely, democratically, and without 
pressure. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

