<DOCNO> FBIS3-8677 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu049_d_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-049 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  14 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statement by President's Office </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103203294 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
1830 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Office of the President of the Slovak 
Republic informed the Press Agency of the Slovak Republic about 
further steps to be taken in connection with the results of 
today's session of the National Council [parliament] of the 
Slovak Republic. 
  As is known, the National Council passed a vote of 
no-confidence in Vladimir Meciar, the current prime minister. 
According to Article 116, Paragraph 6 of the Constitution, on 
the basis of this decision of the National Council, the 
president of the Republic is to recall the prime minister. The 
recall of the prime minister means the resignation of the whole 
government. The president of the Republic is determined to ask 
those members of the government who were not personally subject 
to a vote of no-confidence to temporarily continue exercising 
their duties at the utmost until the naming of the new 
government. The president of the Republic invited Tibor Cabaj, 
the chairman of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
parliamentary group, to negotiate tomorrow morning with the 
strongest parliamentary group about the possibility of creating 
a new government. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

