<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kovac's Resignation Called For </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103184494 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Not only parliament was busy today. It was also 
busy in front of parliament. Several dozen people, who gathered 
there at midday, were joined in the late afternoon by another 
several hundred. According to the latest information, street 
lights have been switched off in front of the National Council 
and in the area between parliament and the Slovak National 
Uprising Square. The crowd that has gathered here is calling on 
the president, among other things, to resign. 

</TEXT>

