<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hungarian MP's Assaulted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103211994 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Several people, helped by about 1,000 sympathizers 
of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia and Vladimir Meciar, 
who gathered in front of the parliament building, have 
physically assaulted Hungarian coalition deputies Vojtech Bugar, 
chairman of the Hungarian Christian Democratic Movement [MKHD], 
and Pal Csaky, chairman of the MKHD-Coexistance parliamentary 
group of deputies. Asked by a reporter from the Press Agency of 
the Slovak Republic why they did not ask for the protection of 
the policemen present, Vojtech Bugar said that the policeman 
whom he addressed said to him to gather 10,000 policemen and 
then he would oblige him. 
  Apart from slogans in support of Vladimir Meciar and the 
government, citizens who gathered in front of the parliament 
building chanted various appeals such as: Tomorrow we will take 
to the streets. 
  Approximately 300 people gathered in Primacialni Square in 
front of President Kovac's residence tonight, calling on him to 
resign. 

</TEXT>

