<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havel on Meciar's Vote of No Confidence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1303110694 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1000 
GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1303110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In today's "Conversation from Lany" to be 
broadcast on the Czech radio at 1315 GMT, President Vaclav Havel 
returns to the vote of no confidence in [Slovak] Prime Minister 
Vladimir Meciar's government. 
  [Havel] It seems to be the culmination of a crisis that has 
lasted on the Slovak political scene for some time now. It is 
difficult to know how it will develop. However, it is probable 
that early elections will take place, and, until then, it is 
hoped that some kind of less conspicuous but efficient 
government will be formed rather soon, which I imagine will be a 
semicaretaker government, one that would bridge the period and 
contribute to calming down the situation. It is in the interest 
of both the Slovak citizens and all of us who are not 
indifferent to developments in Slovakia. [end recording] 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

