<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Walesa Surprised About Pawlak's Visit to Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403115294 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1057 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 14 Mar (PAP)--President Lech Walesa told PAP 
journalists Monday that he was surprised by the announcement of 
Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak's visit to Russia. "Such 
important visits must be consulted upon so that I am not taken 
by surprise," he added. 
  The president said the prime minister is "independent and 
self-governing, but it would be easier if we agreed on such 
matters. I discuss all of my foreign trips with the Mnistry of 
Foreign Affairs, and we need more cooperation here so that we 
can achieve more," the president said. 
  At the same time, Lech Walesa said that, according to 
information he has, Prime Minster Pawlak's visit "is among the 
issues that have been discussed. If new issues are raised and 
if the president is not consulted, the situation could be bad," 
he said. 

</TEXT>

