<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greece Allows Passage of Oil Tankers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103182294 Skopje MIC in English 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1103182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Greece Unexpectedly `Slackens' </F>
Embargo"] 
  [Text] Unexpectedly and without any previous announcement, 
four compositions made up of 79 wagon-cisterns carrying crude 
oil for Macedonia [FYROM--The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia] arrived at the railway crossing Idomeni on the 
Macedonian-Greek border, near Gevgelija. 
  Unofficial sources say two more compositions with 50 
wagon-cisterns loaded with petrol, were expected to arrived in 
the early morning hours of today. Namely, the compositions and 
wagon-cisterns in question were loaded before the blockade, and 
had been waiting to enter Macedonia for 22 days. 

</TEXT>

