<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Resigns; HZDS Enters Into Opposition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403134494 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1300 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At today's meeting in Bratislava, the Slovak 
Government has unanimously decided to end its activity. 
According to another decision, no member of Vladimir Meciar's 
government will accept the president's request to exercise his 
duties until the formation of a new cabinet. 
  The government has also agreed to recall all state 
secretaries [deputy ministers] and all heads of ministerial 
offices by 18 March. Meciar announced that he received two 
letters from the president. In one of the letters, the 
president notified him of his dismissal from the office of the 
prime minister and in the second one, he was asked as the 
chairman of the strongest political party to nominate a 
representative of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] 
who would attempt to form a new government. Meciar emphasized 
that the HZDS was not going to enter into any government and was 
going into opposition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

