<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Forces Attack Lika Defense Lines </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403105094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Just after 0600 this morning the Serb aggressor 
began attacks on the Croatian Army's defense lines on the Lika 
battlefield, the political department of the Gospic operational 
area of the Croatian Army reports. 
  The Serb forces opened heavy artillery fire on the 
residential outskirts of Licko Lesce, and at 1000 the attacks 
were still in progress, Major Darko Dekovic, the assistant 
commander of the Gospic operational area said. According to 
first reports there are no casualties, but damage to residential 
and industrial facilities is huge. The county information 
center in Gospic warned the residents to be cautious. The 
Perusic-Stari Licki Osik-Gospic road is still closed, and 
traffic is diverted onto the Perusic-Klanac-Gospic road. All 
school classes have been cancelled until further notice. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

