<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Army Returns Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1303155794 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1303155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Danko Peric from Knin] </F>
  [Text] The Headquarters of the Serbian Army of Krajina has 
announced that in the past 24 hours, the Croatian Army on 
several occasions has hit Krajina positions and civilian targets 
in Lika, shooting from (?Trle), from where it still has not 
withdrawn. These attacks from infantry and artillery weapons 
were responded to by shooting at the Croatian Army combat 
positions and, it is said in the announcement, great losses have 
been inflicted upon them. 
  When visiting that section of the Lika battlefield, Milan 
Martic, president of the Republic of Serbian Krajina, and Major 
General Milan Celeketic, commander of the Serbian Army of 
Krajina, expressed satisfaction with the development of events. 
After visiting the Kozjan region, Martic and Celeketic met the 
local leadership of Teslingrad, the Lika town that was most 
frequently attacked from Croatian soldiers' positions in this 
war and to which huge material damage has been caused. 
  The Krajina Army General Staff reported that provocations by 
the Croatian Army have also been registered in the Plasko region 
in Lika, Zemunik Gornji, Smiljcic near Benkovac, and Novigrad, 
as well as Kricke and other towns near Drnis and Velika Glava 
near Skradin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

