<F P=102>  LD1203163694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1200 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hungarian President Arpad Goncz has promoted 
Lieutenant-General Janos Deak, Hungarian Army commander and 
chief of staff, to the rank of colonel-general. On the occasion 
of the 15 March holiday, Arpad Goncz promoted 11 colonels, four 
of them to major general and seven of them to brigadier general. 
  This was the first occasion that somebody was promoted to 
the 
rank of brigadier general, a rank established in the Defense Law 
passed in January. Defense Minister Lajos Fur and Interior 
Minister Imre Konya were also present at the ceremony. 

</TEXT>

