<H3> <TI>   Justice Minister Labeled PUNR `Sympathizer' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1403193194 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 11 Mar 
94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> AU1403193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Crina Nedelcu: "Ioan Gavra Admitted That the New </F>
Justice Minister Is a Sympathizer of the PUNR"] 
  [Text] During a National Romanian Unity Party [PUNR] news 
conference held yesterday, [Deputy Party Chairman] Ioan Gavra 
admitted that on 1 March the PUNR leaders examined the 
personalities of the experts proposed [by the government party] 
to take over the leadership of the Justice Ministry and the 
Transportation Ministry, and they supported the persons who were 
appointed as ministers on Sunday [6 March]. 
  Ioan Gavra stated that Iosif Gavril Chiuzbaian was proposed 
as a candidate for the Ministry of Justice by Pavel Suian, 
brother of Valer Suian, first deputy chairman of the party 
[PUNR]. 
  Horia Pop [Brasov PUNR deputy] added: "It cannot be excluded 
that he will join the PUNR in the future." 
  Talking about the second stage of the government reshuffle, 
Gavra asserted that the new ministers will also be technocrats: 
"In the end, the government will consists of more experts than 
Social Democracy Party of Romania members, because we need 
experts to pull the country out of the current crisis." 

</TEXT>

