<H3> <TI>   Serbs Blame Muslims for Death of French Soldier </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403223694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2227 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, Mar 14 (TANJUG) -- Troops of the Fifth 
Corp of the Bosnian Moslem Army are responsible for the death of 
a French peace-keeper killed last Friday near Bihac (western 
Bosnia), the Bosnian Serb News Agency SRNA on Monday evening 
quoted well informed Serb military sources as saying. 
  The sources said that they had obtained the information from 
circles close to the command of the French battalion of the U.N. 
Protection Force (UNPROFOR) stationed in Coralici near Cazin. 
  SRNA recalled that the Serb side was immediately accused of 
being responsible for the death of the French soldier at one of 
the UNPROFOR observation posts on the Bihac front although the 
circumstances and motives for the killing remained unclarified 
until this very day. 

</TEXT>

