<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Attack HVO in Mt Ozren Region </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503115494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1503115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Smajl Terzic from the 7th South Operative Group </F>
Information Center] 
  [Text] Over the past 24 hours, the chetniks from Bajic 
Kamen in the Mt. Ozren region used a B-1 gun to shell the 
village of Sijevo. The enemy is continuously regrouping along 
the entire 133-km long defense line. Moreover, significant 
movements of motorized vehicles have been sighted in the region 
of Kokice and Novi Seher. Our reconnaissance units report that 
the woods in Sijakovac were ablaze all night, and that it was 
Croats and Muslims, mobilized in Doboj and Teslic, who were 
forced to set fire to them. As we file this report, the chetniks 
are fiercely but unsuccessfully attacking units of the (?111th) 
Croatian Defense Council Zepce Brigade. 
  This has been Smajl Terzic reporting from the 7th South 
Operative Group Information Center. 

</TEXT>

