<H3> <TI>   Marjanovic To Address Assembly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503093594 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1503093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Serbian Assembly is to start its first 
regular session today at which it is to elect the new Serbian 
Government. Zoran Vaskovic reports from the Assembly building. 
  [Begin Vaskovic recording] Mirko Marjanovic, prime 
minister-elect, is first expected to present his program and 
propose the ministers for the new government. A debate is 
expected to follow. The vote will be in a package, as the saying 
goes, and secret, unless the deputies decide that the vote 
should be public. The government will be elected if over half 
the deputies in the Assembly, that is, at least 126 deputies, 
decide to give it a vote of confidence. [passage omitted] 
  Radio Belgrade will broadcast in full the presentation of 
Prime Minister-elect Marjanovic. At the moment there are still 
some empty seats in the hall, but the deputies are arriving. 
This is all for now from the Serbian Assembly building. 

</TEXT>

