<H3> <TI>   Milosevic To Help Solve UN Convoy Problems </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503133494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1230 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 15 March (TANJUG) -- The UN High 
Commissioner for Refugees Sadako Ogata has said that her talks 
with Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic "were very 
comprehensive and beneficial." 
  President Milosevic today received Ogata, who is staying in 
our country at the invitation of the federal government. In a 
brief statement after the meeting, Ogata said that she had 
talked with President Milosevic about problems relating to 
humanitarian convoys for ex-Bosnia-Herzegovina and about the 
problem of refugees. 
  Ogata stressed that she had received assurances from 
President Milosevic that he would help in solving the problems 
facing humanitarian convoys. 

