<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HZDS: `Full Confidence' in Meciar as Chairman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203195194 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The analysis of the current political situation 
and preparations of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
[HZDS] for parliamentary and communal elections were the main 
points of today's meeting of the National Presidium of the HZDS 
in Spisska Nova Ves. More from Pavol Sveton: 
  [Begin recording] [Sveton] [passage omitted] We have learned 
from the press secretary, in the course of the HZDS National 
Presidium discussions, that Vladimir Meciar has offered his 
resignation from the position of chairman of the HZDS, this 
being based on yesterday's developments in the parliament. 
However, members of the presidium have expressed their full 
confidence in him. At the following press debate, Vladimir 
Meciar, among other things, said: 
  [Meciar] The movement has confirmed that it is entering into 
opposition and will not enter into any government coalition that 
is now being formed. The movement is dissatisfied with the 
president's activities, with the method he has of carrying out 
his duties, and with the way he has damaged the interests of the 
state and the good name of the Slovak Government. At the same 
time, the movement expresses its concern about the internal 
situation, among the citizens and elsewhere in that the stage is 
becoming more fragmented rather than consolidated. Can you 
imagine the big fight that is about to start, for example, in 
connection with who will propose the prime minister? Peter 
Weiss [chairman of the Party of the Democratic Left (SDL)] 
thinks it will be him and forgot to notice that, behind his 
back, a coalition was formed of Milan Knazko [chairman of the 
Alliance of Democrats of the Slovak Republic], Ludovit Cernak 
[former chairman of the Slovak National Party], and Jan 
Carnogursky [chairman of the Christian Democratic Movement], 
which has gotten more votes than Weiss. Problems are arising in 
the personnel situation. 
  In any case, the movement recommends and the government 
wants 
to apply this recommendation that, after my resignation on 14 
March, the whole government will resign. We do not recommend 
that members of the government accept the president's request to 
continue exercising their duties. The president grossly 
offended members of this government by accusing them of 
corruption. This has spread throughout the world today. He 
cannot ask that these people who were so grossly accused and 
offended accept such appointments. He alone must bear the 
responsibility and consequences. [passage omitted]. 
  Concerning negotiations with other political parties, the 
HZDS is of the opinion that the leadership of the SDL, 
particularly Weiss and Milan Ftacnik [deputy chairman of the 
SDL], is untrustworthy. It broke all agreements that were 
prepared for this action. It will take a very long time for the 
trust of our parties and movements to return for a resumption of 
mutual negotiations, and there is a big question mark over its 
ever becoming possible. 
  I will return to the parliament together with Olga 
Keltosova, 
minister of labor, social affairs, and the family, and Justice 
Minister Katarina Tothova. We shall use all of our capabilities 
to become a strong opposition party. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

