<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NBS Suspends Refinancing Credits for Banks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1403203294 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 11 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1403203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Bankers' Meeting"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--Vladimir Masar, governor of the Slovak 
National Bank [NBS], yesterday informed the highest 
representatives of all commercial banks about topical issues of 
monetary development and the NBS's monetary policy. The meeting 
was attended by other members of the NBS Banking Council. The 
discussion concerned, above all, the temporary suspension by the 
NBS of refinancing credits for commercial banks. This measure 
is a consequence of the growth of liquidity at the beginning of 
this year, caused by the increase of the state budget deficit 
toward the end of 1993. The representatives of commercial banks 
noted that, even though they were not responsible for the growth 
of liquidity, this NBS measure has an unfavorable impact on 
their credit policy toward clients. 

</TEXT>

