<H3> <TI>   Industrial Production Down 1.2 Percent in Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403181894 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary] Rudolf Krc, chairman of the Statistical Office of 
the Slovak Republic, briefed the media today about the 
development of the Slovak economy in January 1994. For example, 
the consumption of the population, assessed on the basis of 
retail trade takings, was just below 16 billion korunas. 
Compared to December 1993, this is a drop of 21 percent. Krc 
said that, compared to December 1993, industrial production 
dropped by 1.2 percent in January. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

