<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman, Granic Meet With Churkin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503094194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
0900 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last night Dr. Franjo Tudjman, president of the 
Republic of Croatia, received special Russian envoy Vitaliy 
Churkin. 
  After the talks, Churkin told journalists that appropriate 
and rapid action is needed to help the three sides in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina find the best solution. He continued: I 
expect that next week we will launch a peace process which might 
finally resolve the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Vitaliy Churkin also had talks with Croatian Foreign 
Minister 
Mate Granic and informed him about his talks in Sarajevo and 
Belgrade with representatives of the Bosnian Serbs and with 
Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic. They agreed that the 
Bosnian Serbs should be included in the negotiations as soon as 
possible in order for an integral solution, as well as peace and 
stability in this region, to be found. 

</TEXT>

