<H3> <TI>   Economy Minister Dyba Recalls Deputy Chrudina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1403185494 Prague CESKY DENIK in Czech 11 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1403185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CESKY DENIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(jpk)": "Dyba Has Recalled His Deputy"] </F>
  [Text] Prague--Economy Minister K. Dyba yesterday relieved 
his deputy, L. Chrudina, from his post and from his obligation 
to perform his duties until the end of March. The minister 
thanked his deputy, who, among other things, had been entrusted 
with drafting a report on telecommunications policy, which has 
been a major liability to Dyba's ministry since January and has 
slowed down the system for privatizing Czech telecommunications. 
Chrudina's recall was formulated "by mutual agreement." 

</TEXT>

