<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Violating Sarajevo Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403234894 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2338 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403234894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, Mar 14 (TANJUG) -- Moslem forces violated 
the ceasefire on the Sarajevo front several times on Monday, 
Bosnian Serb republic military sources said on Monday evening. 
  The command of the Sarajevo-Romania Corps of the Bosnian 
Serb 
army said in a statement that Moslem forces threw hand grenades 
and fired rifle-launched grenades at Serb defense lines on the 
Rajlovac front and that Moslem forces made provocations with 
infantry weapons in the area of Vrbanja Most and at the Ilijas 
front. Moslem snipers were not silent either and their targets 
were the barracks in Rajlovac and in the suburb of Faletici. 
  Moslem units carried out civil engineering works in the area 
of Mrkovic and the Jewish cemetary as well as along the lines of 
separation with the Serb forces on the Ilidza front. The 
Moslems are trying to advance their positions towards the Serb 
forces before the very eyes of UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces], 
which has been acting as a buffer between the warring sides 
following the withdrawal of heavy artillery from the Sarajevo 
area, the statement said. 

</TEXT>

