<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Discussed With FYROM Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503175294 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1503175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 15 March at the Boyana residence, Evgeni 
Matinchev, deputy chairman of the Council of Ministers, and 
Industry Minister Rumen Bikov met Jovan Andonov, deputy prime 
minister for Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM]. 
  The possibility of transit transportation of Macedonian 
goods 
through Bulgaria, cooperation between our enterprises and Skopje 
companies, and the possibility of granting help to Macedonia 
were discussed. 
  The work of the two delegations continues in specialized 
commissions, where issues related to bilateral cooperation in 
transportation, industry, customs control, and road construction 
were specified. 

