<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDS Sets Date for Talks, Supports Early Vote </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503141594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1400 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1503141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Coordinating Council of the Union of 
Democratic Forces [SDS] decided to hold the Sixth SDS National 
Conference on 14-15 May. The forum will discuss issues related 
to the election tactics, the future government, and the SDS's 
partners. 
  It was pointed out that the attitude of the Bulgarian 
Socialist Party [BSP] toward the government is totally 
irresponsible. The country's economic and political situation 
and the questionable status of the cabinet require the urgent 
initiative of President Zhelev, who, according to the SDS, must 
immediately begin consultations with the political forces. 
  The SDS sees the only solution to the situation in the 
country as early elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

