<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO Official Cited on AWACS, Serb Planes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603100194 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0600 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A high-ranking NATO officer has confirmed that the 
AWACS planes patrolling in Hungary's airspace contributed to the 
shooting down two weeks ago of four Serb aircraft that had 
violated the UN air exclusion zone over Bosnia. 
  The NATO European Command's deputy chief of staff 
responsible 
for operations said that NATO was not surprised when Budapest 
asked that no AWACS planes should be in Hungarian airspace at a 
time of a potential NATO air strikes in Bosnia. However, in 
order to have effective intelligence it was necessary for NATO 
to obtain data from the AWACS planes located over Hungary. 
  The general also said that NATO was in constant radio 
contact 
with Hungarian Government organs and the Hungarian military air 
defense leadership. 

</TEXT>

