<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bulgarian Party's Calls for Autonomy Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103185894 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1103185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Autonomy for Pirin Macedonia"] </F>
  [Text] The leader of the Macedonian organization OMO 
Ilenden in Bulgaria Jordan Kostadinov stated during the press 
conference for the agency BALKAN his organization's demand for a 
status of an autonomous region of Pirin Macedonia. He claims 
Bulgaria is forcibly assimilating the Macedonians by not 
acknowledging their language and by physical and moral violence 
by the authorities, which is a kind of a genocide. He added 
claims that Macedonians are in fact Bulgarians is a war 
propaganda, since 75 percent of the population in Pirin 
Macedonia have a sense of belonging to the Macedonian nation. 
  Kostadinov demanded introducing the Macedonian language in 
the schools and Macedonian nation as a category in the passport 
and diplomas. In addition, he insists on separation of the 
Nevrokop diocese of a metropolitan from the Bulgarian Church and 
appointing a Macedonian metropolitan. He also demands the 
Macedonian autonomous region to have a crowned lion in its 
symbol and a sun on its flag. 

</TEXT>

