<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RFE Frequency Withdrawn by Former Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603100094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 0800 
GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tension in the Slovak Republic is growing. Our 
Bratislava correspondent, Renata Havranova, reports in detail: 
  [Havranova] Listeners who wanted to listen to a Radio Free 
Europe [RFE] newscast this morning could not find it on the 
airwaves. 
  Former Minister Hofbauer has implemented his threat, made 
after the editors of this radio station were savagely attacked 
outside the president's office, and withdrew the frequency of 
Radio Free Europe. This was confirmed to me this morning in a 
telephone conversation with (Otto Machac), administrator of the 
Bratislava Office of RFE. He said he had been warned of 
disconnection as early as Monday, but no one had officially 
informed him until now. Otto Machac added that the United 
States, as well as the Munich leadership of RFE, will protest 
against this step. 
  The behavior of the outgoing government is very strange. 
Roman Kovac confirmed to journalists last night that personnel 
purges are continuing at the ministries, privatization is under 
way, and certain property is being written off. 
  According to Roman Kovac, the first step of the new 
government, which has been complete since last night, will be to 
open investigations into these unlawful steps on the part of 
former Prime Minister Meciar and the other members of the former 
government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

