<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Situation on Slovakia Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503143794 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 0600 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Jan Ruml spoke about the situation 
on the Czech-Slovak border following the culmination of the 
political crisis in Slovakia yesterday. Together with his 
departmental colleagues, he is attending a session at Plumlov, 
Prostejov district. 
  He said: 
  [Begin Ruml recording] As for the state border, naturally, 
the talks must be suspended at the moment because they have been 
transformed to the level of political talks, that is the level 
of two governments, two prime ministers. This means that the 
controversial points must be frozen. 
  The border should be delimited in the places where the 
border 
commission was capable of agreeing, and I assume that the next 
Slovak government will be interested in talking about these 
matters and that we will agree in the end on the two parts of 
the state border, above all for the benefit of the people. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

