<F P=102>  AU1603121794 Paris AFP in English 1206 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1603121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sarajevo, March 16 (AFP) -- The formal adoption 
of an accord to reopen roads around the Bosnian capital was 
postponed for a day Wednesday at the request of Bosnian Serb 
officials, the commander of UN forces in Bosnia said. 
  General Michael Rose said the Serbs requested the delay, the 
second in three days, so that experts could be brought in from 
Belgrade. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

