<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   CTK Profiles New Cabinet Members </TI></H3>
<H4>   Deputy Prime Minister Brigita Schmognerova </H4>
<F P=102> AU1703061494 Prague CTK in English 1935 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703061494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- Brigita Schmognerova, 
economist by profession, was appointed Slovak deputy prime 
minister today. 
  Schmognerova was born on November 17, 1947, in Bratislava. 
She graduated from Bratislava's School of Economics (VSE). In 
1974-1976 she completed her postgraduate studies at the Natural 
Science Faculty of Comenius University in Bratislava. Three 
years later she completed an external postgraduate studies at 
VSE with a thesis on economic sciences. 
  In 1971-1976 Schmognerova worked at the VSE National Economy 
Faculty as an expert assistant. Since 1976 she has been 
employed at the Slovak Academy of Science Economics Institute as 
a scientific worker and chief of the Microeconomic Department. 
  After 1989 she was briefly an adviser to a Slovak deputy 
prime minister and later a consultant in a number of commissions 
in the Economy Ministry. Schmognerova is a member of the 
Economic Club of the Democratic Left Party (SDL). 

</TEXT>

