Stavoprojekt company in Trnava, west Slovakia. 
  After November 1989 he was one of the founders of the 
Christian Democratic Movement (KDH) in the Trnava district, and 
has been a KDH deputy since June 1990. Until June 1992 he was 
chairman of the KDH deputies' group, and is now a member of 
parliament's committee for the national economy and the budget. 
  As a deputy, his interests lie in the social field and in 
economics. In the KDH he is responsible for the social field 
and is the creator of the party's social program. 

