Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- The new Slovak minister 
of justice is Milan Hanzel, proposed by the Democratic Left 
Party (SDL). Hanzel is the former state secretary of the 
Justice Ministry. 
  He was born on April 27, 1947 in Kosice, east Slovakia. In 
1970 he graduated from the Law School of the Comenius University 
in Bratislava. In 1984 he gained an external doctorate from the 
Department of Criminal Law, and started teaching in the 
department as an external lecturer. 
  After finishing his military service, he became a justice of 
a military court. From 1972-1989 he practiced in district 
military courts, in 1989 becoming judge and chairman of the 
Higher Military Court in Trencin. 
  He worked on the Advisory Committee of the Slovak 
parliament's Constitutional Committee, and was a member of the 
parliamentary Committee for Petitions, Legal Protection and 
Security. In November 1992 he was appointed state secretary of 
the Justice Ministry. 

