<F P=103> AU1703061094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- In the new Slovak 
Government appointed today, Mikulas Dzurinda from the Christian 
Democratic Movement (KDH) holds the post of Minister of 
Transport, Communications and Public Works. 
  Dzurinda was born on February 4, 1955. He graduated from the 
High School of Transport and Telecommunications in Zilina, 
central Slovakia. He worked in the Zilina-based Transport 
Research Institute, and later at the Bratislava-based Railways 
General Directorate. 
  He helped introduce informatics and automated systems into 
the country's railways. In 1988 he ended his postgraduate 
studies with a thesis. He often published articles concerning 
his profession and lectured on the issue. 
  When the Slovak Transport and Communications Ministry was 
established in 1991, Dzurinda became the economic secretary to 
the minister. He held the post until June 1992. In the June 
1992 elections he was elected a deputy to the Slovak parliament. 
Since then he has been chairing the economic group within the 
KDH and has been the KDH's spokesman for economic questions. 

</TEXT>

