<F P=103> AU1703060894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- Pavel Koncos was 
appointed new Slovak agriculture minister today, at the proposal 
of the Democratic Left Party (SDL). 
  Koncos, chairman of an agricultural cooperative in Klenovec, 
central Slovakia, started to appear on the Slovak political 
scene in 1990. He was elected a parliamentary deputy in the 
June 1992 elections on the SDL slate. 
  Koncos was born on September 28, 1947, in Rimavska Pila, 
central Slovakia. In 1966-1972 he studied at the Agricultural 
School in Nitra, central Slovakia, and then worked as a chief 
economist in a breeding farm in Rimavska Sobota and in 1979 
became chairman of the agricultural cooperative in Klenovec. 
  From 1990 Koncos worked as deputy chairman of the Slovak 
Union of Agricultural Cooperatives. After the establishment of 
the Slovak Agricultural and Food Union in 1991 he was elected 
its chairman. 
  Koncos is actively dealing with agricultural problems in the 
Slovak parliament. In June 1992 he was elected chairman of the 
Parliamentary Committee for Agrarian, Forestry and Water 
Management. 

</TEXT>

