assistant physician at Derer Hospital in Bratislava. 
  In 1971-1987 Sagat was an expert assistant at the Institute 
for Advanced Education for Physicians and Pharmacists. In 
October 1988 he was named director of Derer Hospital in 
Bratislava and dismissed by former Health Minister Sobona on 
June 1, 1993. He continued to work in the hospital as chief 
physician of the pediatrics clinic. 

