<H3> <TI>   Kovac, Ministers Comment on Cabinet, Goals </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kukan on Relations With Prague </H4>
<F P=102> AU1703091894 Prague CTK in English 2237 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington, March 16 (CTK) -- Relations with the 
Czech Republic remain Slovakia's priority number one, newly 
appointed Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan told CTK before 
his departure from New York on Wednesday. 
  Kukan, Slovakia's permanent representative to the UN up to 
date, said Slovak-Czech relations were good and that it was 
necessary to rule out beforehand any possible disputes. 
  Slovak diplomacy will also continue to focus on the gradual 
integration into European structures, creation of good 
neighborly relations and contribution to the country's economic 
development, Kukan said. 
  He said he would also see to the most effective possible 
functioning of the existing diplomatic representations abroad 
whose staffs are limited due to financial reasons. In this 
connection Kukan did not rule dismissals of some diplomats. 

</TEXT>

