<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kovac, Ministers Comment on Cabinet, Goals </TI></H3>
<H4>   Dzurinda To Revitalize Privatization </H4>
<F P=102> AU1603205294 Prague CTK in English 1736 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1603205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 16 (CTK) -- Mikulas Dzurinda, who 
in the new Slovak cabinet is to take the post of minister of 
transport, communications and public works, said today he was 
going first of all to "get the privatization going" of 
communications and railways which had stagnated of late. 
  Speaking to CTK after his meeting with President Michal 
Kovac, Dzurinda said he wanted to proceed according to a concept 
of the development of the Slovak infrastructure which he had 
started before Meciar's government. 
  "I have received signals that a number of privatization acts 
in this field were lately quite strange and I intend to check on 
them thoroughly," he said. 
  "I hold the opinion that a new government should suspend the 
privatization decisions the previous cabinet took after February 
15 and to check them before proceeding to its own activity in 
this field," Dzurinda said. 
  Asked how he intended to solve the conflict of former 
Transport Minister Roman Hofbauer with the Radio Free Europe 
(RFE) Dzurinda said that if it became clear that the outgoing 
cabinet tried to stop RFE broadcasting in Slovakia then he would 
see that it was resumed as soon as possible and the matter 
settled so that RFE could broadcast in the future in an 
absolutely calm atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

