<H3> <TI>   RFE Broadcasting After `Unlawful' Stoppage </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703092094 Prague CTK in English 2228 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 16 (CTK) -- Radio Free Europe 
(RFE) resumed its broadcasts in Slovakia today, at 3:00 PM, 
Director of Slovak Telecommunications Vladimir Ondrovic told 
journalists. 
  He said that the stoppage of RFE broadcasts decided on 
Tuesday by Vladimir Zeman, chief director of the 
Telecommunication Department in the Transport Ministry, was 
unlawful and contradicted the valid agreement. He said that any 
interference in the current state could be made merely by the 
competent parties -- the Slovak telecommunications and RFE. 
  Slovak officials on Tuesday stopped relaying RFE broadcasts 
from two transmitters, in violation of the still valid 
agreement providing for medium-wavelength RFE broadcasts. 

</TEXT>

