Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Appeal in Support of Referendum"] </F>
  [Text] "Esteemed citizens, with your help we established 
the Slovak Republic as a sovereign state. We regret that we 
were unable to complete, with your support, the work that we 
strove to accomplish. We are confident that you will not forget 
this. Together with you, we are determined to realize our plans 
and aims. We are still keen on your support and favor. We will 
do everything in our power to achieve the aims outlined by Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar in his address to the National Council 
of the Slovak Republic on 11 March 1994. In the interest of a 
democratic Slovak Republic, give your support to the 
referendum!" This is stated in a Slovak Government statement 
that was made available to the TA SR yesterday evening. 

