<H3> <TI>   Editor Protests Ministry Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603203294 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Anna Samelova, editor of Slovak radio's Radiozurnal, 
has strongly protested against the statement made by Peter 
Kuchar, spokesman of the Interior Ministry of the Slovak 
Republic, to the effect that some journalists used the events at 
the Primatial Square on Monday, 14 March, to compromise the 
police. 
  On that day at the Primatial Square, an unknown man hit 
Samelova in the face with his fist. She asked a policeman 
standing next to her for help. To her request, he replied: I 
am not here. 
  The Radiozurnal editor denies that, at the beginning of the 
Monday evening edition of Radiozurnal, she used the information 
to politically compromise the police. She merely described what 
happened at the square during a public radio broadcast. 
However, she does not see the fact that she decided not to 
press charges as a reason not to investigate the events and draw 
appropriate conclusions on the part of competent bodies. 

</TEXT>

