<H3> <TI>   No Intention of Blocking Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603183094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1700 
GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Czech Government has discussed the expected 
visit by Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of 
Russia, to the Czech Republic, and has decided that it will not 
try to prevent it. 
  [Begin Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus recording] Since there is 
no visa requirement for Russian citizens, the government does 
not have any legal means that would enable it to prevent Mr. 
Zhirinovskiy from entering the territory of the Czech Republic 
[words indistinct]. The government does not intend to find a way 
round our laws and therefore it will act in this way. 
  Naturally, the government is ready to intervene if any of 
our 
laws are violated or if public order is disturbed, etc. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

