<H3> <TI>   Government, Serbs Sign Sarajevo Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703152394 Paris AFP in English 1503 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1703152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, March 17 (AFP) -- The Bosnian Government 
and Bosnian Serbs on Thursday signed an agreement to open roads 
and partially lift the siege of the Bosnian capital Sarajevo, 
officials announced. 
  Under the UN-sponsored agreement, Sarajevo will be linked by 
road to central Bosnia-Herzegovina via the Moslem majority town 
of Visoko (25 kilometres) to the west and other road corridors 
will be opened. 

