foreign affairs; Milan Hanzel minister of justice; Lubomir 
Harach minister of education; Lubo Roman minister of culture; 
Tibor Sagat minister of health care; Julius Brocka minister of 
labor, social affairs, and family; and Juraj Hrasko minister of 
the environment. 
  After the government was appointed, the new ministers were 
sworn in by the president of the Republic and confirmed their 
oath with their signatures. 

