<F P=102>  AU1603195294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1603195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A consultative meeting of the Presidency and the 
government was held in the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency 
building today, with only one item on the agenda -- scrutiny of 
the constitutional solution for the Federal Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the signing of the agreement with the 
Republic of Croatia. 
  The meeting was chaired by Bosnia-Herzegovina Deputy Prime 
Minister Edib Bukvic. Several suggestions were put forward in 
the debate that will be conveyed to our negotiators. It is 
expected that the Washington agreement will be signed by 
Presidents Izetbegovic and Tudjman, to be subsequently ratified 
by the deputies of our assembly. 
  The Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly session is expected to take 
place at the end of this month. 

