<H3> <TI>   Csurka Supports Free Press </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603094894 Budapest MTI in English 1932 GMT 15 Mar 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1603094894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 15 March (MTI) -- The Hungarian Justice 
and Life Party, the Hungarian Way groups, and several other 
organizations held a joint ceremony to mark March 15, the 
anniversary of the outbreak of the 1848-49 Hungarian revolution, 
on Tuesday [15 March]. Several thousand people attended the 
ceremony, held in Szabadsag Square, in front of the Hungarian 
Television building. 
  The co-chairman of the Hungarian Justice and Life Party, 
Istvan Csurka, said the Hungarian nation is in extreme peril, 
threatened by internal deterioration, with the front line drawn 
between the Hungarian national character and a foreign national 
character. Csurka said the former system is ideologically still 
in place, and there is major financial backing for attacks on 
the national character. 
  "We want a free Hungarian press, in which left-wing lies 
presented as truth are eliminated, and from which the 
falsification of history and anti-Hungarian attitudes are 
banished," Csurka said. 

</TEXT>

