<H3> <TI>   Nastase on Party Talks, Government Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503203794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1628 GMT 15 Mar 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1503203794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 15/3/1994 -- Adrian Nastase, 
executive chairman of the ruling Party of Social Democracy 
[PDSR] "has disclosed" at a March 15 press conference that his 
party was willing to negotiate with both left and right, with a 
view to promote the general interests of the country. Adrian 
Nastase said that the difficult economic and political problems 
of 1994 could be solved only by applying the arithmetic resulted 
from the 1992 polls. In his opinion it is not a certain 
composition of the executive that is essential at present, but a 
governing programme based on the provisions of the memorandum 
with the IMF, and the speeding of the reform. According to the 
ruling party that can be achieved, added Nastase, by the 
creation of a group of experts made up of representatives of all 
parliamentary parties, apt to attract the interest of all 
political parties. 
  Referring to snap elections, Adrian Nastase said that they 
would be "disastrous" for the country. 

</TEXT>

