<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Government Crisis </TI></H3>
<H4>   HZDS Members Consider Roles </H4>
<F P=102> AU1103205094 Prague CTK in English 2022 GMT 11 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1103205094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 11 (CTK) -- "We have received 
signals from the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) that 
some of its members are willing to contemplate their 
participation in the new government," chairman of the Democratic 
Left Party (SDL) Peter Weiss said. 
  Chairman of the HZDS deputies group Tibor Cabaj commented on 
it as follows: "I doubt they are from our group because the HZDS 
leadership adopted a resolution, whereby in the case of the 
dismissal of the government we would turn into opposition." 
  Cabaj said he could not rule out that this could happen. 
These deputies should reconsider their further HZDS membership. 
It is undignified to wait for expulsion, he said. 
  It is the duty of the SDL to join the provisional 
government, 
regardless of its composition, said Weiss. But it will be, 
indeed, a temporary government because the SDL feels very 
strongly about early elections, Weiss added. 
  Anton Hrnko, a deputy for the National Democratic Club said: 
"I believe that Vladimir Meciar will keep his written promise he 
gave to his daughter that if he is dismissed for the second 
time, he will never return to politics." 

</TEXT>

