<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Government Crisis </TI></H3>
<H4>   Government Holds Final Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> AU1403145594 Prague CTK in English 1316 GMT 14 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1403145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 14 (CTK) -- Outgoing Slovak Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar told journalists today that he had 
received two letters from President Michal Kovac. In the first 
one Kovac informed him of his dismissal and in the second one 
asked him as chairman of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
(HZDS), the strongest political party, to name a HZDS 
representative to form a new cabinet. Meciar said that the HZDS 
would not participate in any government and went into opposition. 
  The Slovak Government ended its activity at its meeting 
today, Meciar said. A vote of no-confidence in his government 
was passed by parliament on Friday. He said the government 
unanimously voted to end its activity, as according to the 
constitution the prime minister's resignation forces the 
government to resign. 
  According to the resolution adopted at the last government 
meeting, none of Meciar's cabinet will accept the president's 
offer to stay in office until a new cabinet is appointed. The 
government decided to recall all its state secretaries and heads 
of administration in all fields. 

</TEXT>

