<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Government Crisis </TI></H3>
<H4>   Moravcik Charged With Forming Cabinet </H4>
<F P=102> AU1503131094 Prague CTK in English 1148 GMT 15 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1503131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava March 15 (CTK) -- Slovak President 
Michal Kovac today officially entrusted Jozef Moravcik the task 
of conducting negotiations on the composition of a new cabinet, 
Kovac's spokesman Anton Bodis told CTK on Tuesday [15 March]. 
  On Monday [14 March], most of the former opposition 
parliamentary parties agreed to propose Moravcik, the foreign 
minister of the former cabinet of Vladimir Meciar, as the new 
Slovak premier. 
  President Kovac asked the former opposition parties to 
compose a new government after the Meciar-led Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) had not answered his question whether 
it would propose a person whom he could charge with the 
composition of the new cabinet. 
  The new cabinet of Premier Designate Moravcik is to be 
completed on Wednesday [16 March] at the latest, when the 
current parliamentary session is to resume. 

</TEXT>

