<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Vojvodina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hungary's Jeszenszky Visits To Mark 15 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1303135394 Budapest MTI in English 1738 GMT 12 Mar 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1303135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ada, March 12 (MTI) -- Hungarian Foreign Minister 
Geza Jeszenszky, who is paying an unofficial visit to Vojvodina, 
arrived in Ada on Saturday afternoon [12 March]. He held talks 
with leaders of the Democratic Community of Vojvodina 
Hungarians, then travelled to Mol, the headquarters of the Vox 
Humana aid organization. 
  Jeszenszky is visiting Vojvodina to mark March 15, and will 
attend the ceremonies honouring the anniversary. He will also 
hold talks with Radoslav Bulajic, the first deputy of the 
federal foreign minister. 
  In a brief statement to MTI's correspondent, Jeszenszky said 
March 15 is particularly important for the Hungarians in 
Vojvodina. In 1848, there was fighting in Vojvodina during the 
Hungarian freedom fight (the area was part of Hungary at the 
time), and national conflicts, but the possibility of the 
solution was also outlined at that time. This should be sought 
today, too, from history, but much more so from the present. 
  In answer to a question on the autonomy possibility of 
Vojvodina Hungarians, Jeszenszky said that in the course of his 
meeting with the leader of the Democratic Community of Vojvodina 
Hungarians, he inquired about any developments in this matter 
since his visit to Belgrade. 
  Jeszenszky then travelled on to Subotica, where a ceremony 
will be held on Saturday evening to mark March 15. 

</TEXT>

