<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nine Deputies Urge U.S. To Lift Cuba Blockade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503211394 Prague CTK in English 1926 GMT 15 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1503211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 15 (CTK) -- Nine Communist Party 
parliamentary deputies have signed a letter drafted by their 
party and sent on Monday [14 March] to the United States 
Congress in support of a congressional initiative to lift 
America's 35-year-old blockade of Cuba. 
  In informing CTK about the letter, however, the chairman of 
the party's deputies group, Vaclav Exner, said it would have 
been better if more deputies had signed it. 
  "A number of deputies from the Social Democratic, Liberal 
Social Union and Left Bloc deputies groups have expressed their 
view that in essence they support ending the blockade of Cuba," 
Exner said. "But it bothers them to a certain extent that the 
suggestion came from our group." 
  The Congressional initiative is being led by Representative 
Charles Rangel, who is expected to present it formally this week. 

</TEXT>

