<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visits Constanta, Black Sea Coast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603135994 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1603135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The military delegation headed by Army General 
Vitaliy Radeskyy, Ukrainian defense minister, arrived in 
Constanta this morning. The Ukrainian guests were received by 
the head of the Chief of Staff of the Romanian Navy, Vice 
Admiral Gheorghe Anghelescu. The Ukrainian delegation's 
schedule also included visits to the destroyer Marasesti, to the 
Mircea cel Batran Navy Academy, and to the Romanian sea coast, 
our correspondent Mircea Lamba reports. 
  The Ukrainian defense minister will be received later today 
by Romanian President Ion Iliescu and by Foreign Affairs 
Minister Teodor Melescanu. 

</TEXT>

