<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Cooperation Treaty Signed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703170794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1400 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1703170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An agreement on military cooperation between 
Romania and Ukraine was signed today by Gheorghe Tinca, Romanian 
minister of national defense, and General Vitaliy Radeskyy, 
Ukrainian minister of national defense. 
  At a subsequent news conference, Tinca said that the treaty 
covers a large sphere of activities of cooperation in the 
military, scientific, and educational spheres. In his turn, 
General Vitaliy Radeskyy expressed the hope that good 
cooperation between the armies of the two countries can 
contribute to good cooperation in the political sphere, 
something which both Romania and Ukraine can put to their use in 
the future. 

</TEXT>

