<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDSR, PAC Conclude Round of Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703193794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1703193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The first round of exploratory talks between the 
Social Democracy Party of Romania [PDSR] and the Civic Alliance 
Party [PAC] concluded a short while ago at Elisabeta Palace. 
  We agreed that both political parties ought to contribute to 
the lessening of tension in Romanian political life, not merely 
at the parliamentary but also at the local administration level. 
We also agreed to cooperate with respect to draft bill packages 
and programs, stated PDSR Deputy Chairman Liviu Maior at a short 
news conference that followed the meeting. The next round of 
talks is scheduled for 29 March. 
  PAC Deputy Chairman Nicolae Taran stated that, quote, we 
established what we could jointly do and how long it would take 
us to achieve those things. The PAC is a member of the 
Democratic Convention of Romania [CDR] and therefore it cannot 
decide in the name of the CDR, but merely pledge things that it 
can achieve on its own. However, our position expressed today 
actually outlined the position of the CDR, unquote, our 
correspondent Florin Brusten reports. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
